<font color="#FF0000">KEEP THE PAINT.  I LIKE IT</font><br>
<tt>Mon Sep  1  0:01:09 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Ed,<br><br>
We were men then, maybe before our time, and men now.  What we have gained is wisdom.  Memories are what we have when there is more behind than there is in the future.  We give what we have learned to our children.<br><br>
I have never talked of the war with my boys nor have I tried to make them warriors.  It is a choice from the heart.  Neither have walked my path and both are giants in their own way.  No matter what we were or what we are now we will leave a legacy of which we can be proud.<br><br>
If people do not understand that even as men we must play then they have forgotten much.  We forget our youth too soon and are unable to see our future.  To see our past as part of what we are is a must otherwise we view our life as a failure.  We must achieve balance as you have said.<br><br>
We are not failures in any description.<br><br>
Save the watch.  I don't want to be the only one that has a five pound ten dial watch they glows from a radioactive dial.<br><br>
Throttling back.  Join on wing brother.  The air is smooth tonight.
<p><code>--   (SW) </code><p>


